Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

Testing a case where there is no content-length header (transfer-encoding: chunked):

$ curl -vvv -H 'x-auth-token: 9fe9dea8487641cf819a76e96174ce00' -X DELETE http://localhost:9292/v2/images/7c2a184c-aa54-426a-9389-793b8ffb7919 -d '123' -H 'transfer-encoding: chunked' -H 'content-length:'


A 400 isn't returned -- we get the previous 204 behaviour.


 T 127.0.0.1:33624 -> 127.0.0.1:9292 [AP]
 DELETE /v2/images/7c2a184c-aa54-426a-9389-793b8ffb7919 HTTP/1.1.
 User-Agent: curl/7.35.0.
 Host: localhost:9292.
 Accept: */*.
 x-auth-token: 9fe9dea8487641cf819a76e96174ce00.
 transfer-encoding: chunked. 
 Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded.
 .
 3.
 123.
 0.
 .

 ##
 T 127.0.0.1:9292 -> 127.0.0.1:33624 [AP]
 HTTP/1.1 204 No Content.
 Content-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8.
 Content-Length: 0.
 X-Openstack-Request-Id: req-req-6ac3724c-cabc-4a24-a412-5df60a1f2a96.
 Date: Tue, 04 Aug 2015 16:34:39 GMT.
 .


This may be because webob doesn't set 'is_body_readable' for nouns other than PUT/POST, so the has_body function doesn't seem to work for these cases.
We should see if it's possible to return 400 in cases also. (TBH I'm not sure if it will be.)
